{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwaMsgK5STRMNxTkRzbF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Nice — race conditions in fixture setup are among the most annoying to track down precisely because they're intermittent. A lock around the shared file is the right call when tests share fixture state.\n\nOne thing worth a quick sanity check, since you're already in there: a file lock serializes access, but if the tests were *contending* over that shared file, the lock fixes the corruption while potentially masking that they have a shared-state dependency at all. If it's cheap to give each test its own fixture file (e.g. a temp file per test / per worker), that removes the contention entirely rather than serializing around it — and keeps the suite parallelizable. If isolation isn't practical here, the lock is the pragmatic fix and totally fine.\n\nEither way, good afternoon's work — that's a real bug you closed, not just a flaky-test suppression. Want me to look at the fixture code and see whether per-test isolation is feasible, or are you happy with the lock?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5329,"cache_read_input_tokens":15171,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5329},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"08332f42-1b7a-4c00-9fb6-db6cb6701574","uuid":"67238b92-6150-4d25-b6f4-60634832c890","request_id":"req_011CcwaMrvvBF8tLhN84mCww"}
